    "slug": "prominent-somali-poet-aadan-tarabi-jaamac-dies-in-hargeysa",
    "summary": "Renowned Somali poet and playwright Aadan Tarabi Jaamac has passed away in Hargeysa. He was 78 and known for his extensive contributions to Somali oral and performing arts.",
    "content": "Aadan Tarabi Jaamac, one of Somalia’s most celebrated poets and playwrights, died in Hargeysa on Wednesday, his family confirmed. The artist was 78 years old and had been a towering figure in Somali literature and performing arts for decades.\n\nBorn in 1948 near the town of Caynaba in the Sool region, Tarabi grew up in a period of significant political change. His father worked as a driver for the governor of the Northwestern region during British colonial rule, giving Tarabi early exposure to administrative and cultural shifts in Somali society.\n\nTarabi’s creative work spanned songs, plays, and poetry. He was known for blending traditional Somali poetic forms with modern themes, earning him a place among the most influential cultural figures in the Horn of Africa. His pieces often reflected social issues, love, and national identity.\n\nFor the Somali diaspora, Tarabi’s work served as a cultural anchor, preserving the Somali language and heritage in communities abroad. His death marks the loss of a key link to Somalia’s rich artistic legacy, particularly for younger generations born outside the country.\n\nRead the original report from Goobjoog here: https://goobjoog.com/2026/07/22/kumuu-ahaa-abwaan-aadan-tarabi-jaamac/",
